<subSubSection pageId="373" pageNumber="374" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="373" pageNumber="374">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="373" pageNumber="374">
This species ranges from South Dakota (Maddison and Swanson 2010: 28) and eastern Wyoming (Lavigne 1977: 44, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1857" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="373" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lugubre">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="373" pageNumber="374">Bembidion lugubre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) south to Costa Rica (Erwin 1982b: 469, Fig. 65).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
